What are 2 BF approaches here?
Should the next greater number be strictly i+1 or it can be i+n?
Can I use Map?
Can I sort nums1?
Should I build a new stack for an each iteration over nums1? Or should start search from the right for an each iteration (if I just imitate the stack by having a pointer)?
How can the problem be classified so that the pattern is applicable for number of tasks?
nums1 = [1, 4, 2]

nums2 = [1, 3, 4, 2]

nums2 = [5, 4, 3, 2, 1, 6] // all of except 6 are what?

nums2 = [9, 8, 7, 10, 3, 2, 1, 4] // what does this example demonstrate?

How can I improve this BF using Stack?
Map&lt;Integer, Integer&gt; map = new HashMap&lt;&gt;();

for(int i = nums2.length - 1; i &gt;= 0; i--)
{
	for(int j = i; j &gt;= 0; j--)
	{
		if(nums2[j] &lt; nums2[i])
		{
			map.put(nums2[j], nums2[i]);
		}
	}
}
